        <p class="text-primary-900 mb-4">
          The healthcare situation is a major draw. CAJA provides a safety net that costs a fraction of US insurance,
          while private hospitals offer world-class care at reasonable prices. The dual-system approach—mandatory CAJA
          plus optional private insurance—gives expats flexibility and comprehensive coverage.
        </p>
        <p class="text-primary-900">
          The 7-year path to citizenship is longer than some alternatives, and Costa Rica doesn't offer citizenship by
          investment. But for those who actually want to live here—enjoying the Pura Vida lifestyle, proximity to the
          US, and a welcoming expat community—it's a compelling option. Just budget accordingly: Costa Rica isn't cheap
